1. Find the first element in the list that is larger than any of the elements in the list. This element is called the pivotal element.
2. Find the rightmost element in the list that is smaller than the pivotal element. This element is called the last element.
3. Move the pivotal element to the end of the list, and move all elements between it and the last element to one position before it in the list.
4. Repeat steps 2 and 3 until all elements have been moved into their final position.
